<br>
If it means anything, my unbuffed AC is 879 at 51.  I'm only now coming up to upgrading my armour to Deepwater and so on, and it still cleans out my bank *grins*  You're damned lucky if you can buy them at your stage. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A> at: 10/21/02 10:28:05 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usevlin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sevlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/02 1:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The quested sol-ro temple armor ..</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the replies!  Looking at some of the stats on the Ro armor, I wonder where I originally got the idea the AC wasn't higher than most of my armor -- it's certainly higher than the lightcrawler arms, legs, and bracer I'm wearing!<br>
<br>
I've definitely been planning to get the Helm of Ro.  (RP wise it's fun playing a gnome; stat-wise, 83 WIS with items is pretty sad.)  Conveniently enough, I've obtained most of what's required for Ro armor even without consciously working on the quest!  (Had all I need for helm and boots, save for the Sand of Ro -- some of which, I bought off Bakanome as early as yesterday morning. *grins*)<br>
<br>
Crustacean is also something I've been looking at.  Although the stat decreases scare me, most of it's -CHA.  I suppose travelling with an enchantress makes that less of an issue.  And even the -DEX shouldn't be too bad, as it's already fairly high -- around 116 right now, I think.  The trade off would be reaking of fish...<br>
<br>
Ro armor costs about 200pp per piece for the plat bars, and maybe some more since I'll probably want to buy the melatite in the Bazaar (rather than take faction hits), but I could probably afford to throw out my lightcrawler, and replace it with some Ro, and maybe a piece of Crustacean or two.<br>
<br>
